<score-partwise>
  <work>
    <work-title>No, Not One!</work-title>
  </work>
  <identification>
    <creator type="composer">Words: Johnson Oatman, Jr, 1894.
Music: 'No, Not One' George Crawford Hugg, 1894.  Setting: "Pentecostal Hymns, No. 2", 1894.
copyright: public domain.  This score is a part of the Open Hymnal Project, 2012 Revision.</creator>
    <encoding>
      <encoder>abc2xml version 268</encoder>
      <software>https://wim.vree.org/svgParse/abc2xml.html</software>
      <encoding-date>2026-07-21</encoding-date>
    </encoding>
    <source>Music source: "Pentecostal Hymns, No. 2" 1898 page 1.   Setting and hymn identical to that found in "Pentecostal Hymns, Nos. 1 and 2 combined", 1894 Hymn 305.  ABC file contributed to the Open Hymnal by Samuel Cantrell, 18 Jan 2012.
not sure about first printing of this hymn; 1894 is earliest verifiable source.  Hugg owned the copyright.  Hugg printed hymnals in 1862, 1879, and 1892.  Suspect hymn is found in one of them.</source>
  </identification>
